d out this mistake of Droṇācārya’s so that he might be alert and uncompromising in the fighting. By this he wanted to point out also that he should not be similarly lenient in battle against the Pāṇḍavas, who were also Droṇācārya’s affectionate students. Arjuna, especially, was his most affectionate and brilliant student. Duryodhana also warned that such leniency in the fight would lead to defeat.50:[\"$\",\"div\",\"203-purport,203-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:lead"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"ing-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-208\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:2:child_items:4:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$106\"}}]}]]]}]\n51:[\"$\",\"div\",\"209-devanagari,209-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-210\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"अत्र श‍ूरा महेष्वासा भीमार्जुनसमा युधि ।\u003cbr/\u003eयुयुधानो विराटश्च द्रुपदश्च महारथः ॥ ४ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\n52:[\"$\",\"div\",\"209-verse_text,209-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-211\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:3:child_items:1:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$