ṁ pakṣe janārdanaḥ.\u003c/em\u003e Victory is always with persons like the sons of Pāṇḍu because Lord Kṛṣṇa is associated with them. And whenever and wherever the Lord is present, the goddess of fortune is also there because the goddess of fortune never lives alone without her husband. Therefore, victory and fortune were awaiting Arjuna, as indicated by the transcendental sound produced by the conchshell of Viṣṇu, or Lord Kṛṣṇa. Besides that, the chariot on which both the friends were seated had been donated by Agni (the fire-god) to Arjuna, and this"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1," indicated that this chariot was capable of conquering all sides, wherever it was drawn over the three worlds.\"}}]}]]]}]\n84:[\"$\",\"div\",\"271-devanagari,271-devanagari\",{\"className\":\"av-devanagari\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Devanagari\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-272\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:14:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-lg text-center\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"पाञ्चजन्यं हृषीकेशो देवदत्तं धनञ्जयः ।\u003cbr/\u003eपौण्ड्रं दध्मौ महाशङ्खं भीमकर्मा वृकोदरः ॥ १५ ॥\"}}]}]]]}]\n85:[\"$\",\"div\",\"271-verse_text,271-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L41\",\"child-273\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:14:child_items:1:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003epāñcajanyaṁ hṛṣīkeśo\u003cbr /\u003edevadattaṁ dhanañ-jayaḥ\u003cbr /\u003epauṇḍraṁ dadhmau 